snippet.textDisplay:
U-235 is the fissile isotope used as bomb fuel in Little Boy. It makes up less than 1% of the U atoms in natural uranium ore and must be somehow concentrated to make reactor fuel, or even more concentrated to make bomb fuel. That’s hard to do because it’s chemically identical with the 99% population of U-238 with a tiny bit less mass from the three fewer neutrons. The higher the proportion of U-235 / U-238 the more materially efficient the fission reaction, the bigger the boom-boom.

Nobody rocks a rumpled suit like my man J. Robert.

snippet.textDisplay: Wow, major props to Nice Peter in this battle for that acting. He totally nailed the despairing look in the start, then the transition into tranquil fury, and the desperation at "but I do what I must". EpicLLOYD did an excellent job with Thanos as well, that menace and confidence, and his camp is a great contrast with Nice Peter. Major props to everyone for putting this together, the lyrics and the visuals. This one is going into my personal list of top rap battles.
